What is a Cluster in Kubernetes?

A Kubernetes cluster is a group of machines (nodes) that work together to run containerized applications.

Think of it as one big system, even though it is made of many computers.

Main Parts of a K8s Cluster
1ï¸âƒ£ Control Plane (Master)

This is the brain of the cluster.

Decides what should run

Schedules Pods on nodes

Manages cluster state

Key components:

API Server

Scheduler

Controller Manager

etcd (cluster database)

2ï¸âƒ£ Worker Nodes

These are the machines that actually run your application.

Run Pods and containers

Have:

kubelet

container runtime (Docker / containerd)

kube-proxy

Simple Flow

You give instructions â†’ Control Plane
Apps run â†’ Worker Nodes

Easy Example

1 cluster

1 master node

3 worker nodes

Your app runs as Pods across those workers

One-Line Interview Answer

â€œA Kubernetes cluster is a set of master and worker nodes that work together to deploy, manage, and scale containerized applications.â€

