What is kubelet?

kubelet is an agent that runs on every worker node in a Kubernetes cluster.

Its main job is to make sure Pods are running exactly as the Control Plane says.

What does kubelet do?
1ï¸âƒ£ Talks to Control Plane

kubelet continuously talks to the API Server

It asks:
ğŸ‘‰ â€œWhich Pods should run on my node?â€

2ï¸âƒ£ Creates & Manages Pods

When it gets Pod info:

Pulls container images

Starts containers using container runtime (Docker / containerd)

Restarts containers if they crash

3ï¸âƒ£ Health Checking

Monitors Pod & container health

Reports status back to Control Plane

4ï¸âƒ£ Node Management

Reports:

CPU usage

Memory usage

Node status (Ready / NotReady)

What kubelet does NOT do âŒ

It does not schedule Pods

It does not talk directly to etcd

It does not manage other nodes

(Scheduler does scheduling, kubelet only executes)

Simple Flow (easy to remember)
Control Plane â†’ kubelet â†’ Containers

Real-Life Example ğŸ­

Control Plane = Manager

kubelet = Supervisor

Containers = Workers

Manager says:
â€œRun 3 workers on this machineâ€
Supervisor (kubelet) makes it happen.

